# Lean In Connect — Cursor Rules
# Design Engineer Assessment by Hrithik Sanyal

## Stack
Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript strict, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui Nova preset,
Framer Motion, Supabase, Anthropic Claude claude-sonnet-4-6, Vercel, Lucide React, DM Sans font.

## Absolute Rules
1. Zero hardcoded hex values. All colors via Tailwind token classes.
2. Zero inline styles.
3. Named exports only. No default exports from components.
4. No 'any' TypeScript types. Ever.
5. All AI calls in API routes only. Never in client components.
6. No .then(). Always async/await.
7. No console.log in final code.
8. No <img> tags. Always next/image.

## Component Structure
- atoms/ → single element, no composition
- molecules/ → 2+ atoms, single responsibility
- organisms/ → full sections
- ui/ → shadcn components, never manually edited

## Props Pattern
Every component gets a named Props interface:
interface ButtonProps { ... }
export function Button({ ... }: ButtonProps) { ... }

## Tailwind Token Classes
Use these class names (configured in tailwind.config.ts):
Colors: bg-brand, bg-brand-hover, bg-surface, bg-subtle, bg-muted
Text: text-default, text-secondary, text-muted, text-inverse, text-brand
Border: border-default, border-strong, border-brand, border-focus
Shadows: shadow-card, shadow-card-hover, shadow-modal

## Framer Motion Pattern
Card entrance:
  initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 12 }}
  animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
  transition={{ duration: 0.3, ease: 'easeOut' }}

Stagger parent:
  variants={{ show: { transition: { staggerChildren: 0.06 } } }}

Card hover:
  whileHover={{ y: -2 }}
  transition={{ duration: 0.15 }}

## API Route Pattern
export async function GET() {
  try {
    // logic
    return NextResponse.json({ data: result })
  } catch (error) {
    return NextResponse.json({ error: 'message' }, { status: 500 })
  }
}

## AI Route Pattern
import Anthropic from '@anthropic-ai/sdk'
const client = new Anthropic({ apiKey: process.env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY })
const message = await client.messages.create({
  model: 'claude-sonnet-4-6',
  max_tokens: 1024,
  system: 'You are helping women advance their careers...',
  messages: [{ role: 'user', content: prompt }]
})

## Mission
Every output — copy, empty states, AI responses, job listings —
should feel warm, specific, and empowering for women navigating
their careers. Never generic. Never corporate. Always human.